Miller Industries, Inc. (NYSE:MLR) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsMiller Industries, Inc. (NYSE:MLR) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume
July 25, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



837 shares changed hands on Tuesday.  Overall, volume was down 97.70% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 Here are some other firms who have updated their holdings.   Rothschild Investment Corp /il augmented its position by buying 550 shares an increase of 0.8% as of 06/30/2017. Rothschild Investment Corp /il currently owns 72,915 shares with a value of $1,812,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 5.0%. As of quarter end Morgan Stanley had bought  a total of 25,717 shares growing its holdings by 467.6%. The value in dollars went from $145,000 to $823,000 a change of $678,000 quarter to quarter.
 Goldman Sachs Group Inc cut its holdings by shedding 5,154 shares a decrease of 18.5% from 12/31/2016 to 03/31/2017. Goldman Sachs Group Inc claims 22,753 shares valued at $600,000. The value of the position overall is down by 18.7%. As of the end of the quarter State Street Corp had acquired 13,846 shares growing its position 5.7%. The value of the investment in Miller Industries, Inc. increased from $6,416,000 to $6,757,000 increasing 5.3% for the reporting period.        Advertisement






 The company is now up by 0.59% since yesterday’s close of $25.45.  The company declared a dividend for shareholders that was paid on Tue Jun 20, 2017.  The dividend was $0.180 per share for the quarter or $0.72 annualized.  This dividend represents a yield of $2.80.  The ex-dividend date was set for Friday the 9th of June 2017. 
 Shares last traded at $25.60 which is marginally over the 50 day moving average of $25.50 and which is a tad above the 200 day moving average of $25.33.  The 50 day moving average was up by +0.41% whereas the 200 day moving average was up $0.27 or +1.05%. 
 The P/E ratio is currently 14.30 and the market cap is 290.59M. 
 Miller Industries, Inc., launched on April 28, 1994, is a manufacturer of towing and recovery equipment. The Company manufactures the bodies of wreckers and car carriers, which are installed on truck chassis manufactured by third parties. It has offices in Ooltewah, Tennessee, domestic manufacturing operations in Tennessee and Pennsylvania, and foreign manufacturing operations in France and the United Kingdom. The Company purchases truck chassis for resale its customers. The Company also manufactures vehicle transport trailers. As of December 31, 2016, the Business’s products were sold through independent distributors all 50 states, Canada and Mexico, and other foreign markets including Europe, the Pacific Rim, the Middle East, South America and Africa, and through prime contractors to governmental entities. The Business’s products are offered under various brands, including Century, Vulcan, Challenger, Holmes, Champion, Chevron, Eagle, Titan, Jige and Boniface..
        Advertisement




