            Miller Industries is the world's largest manufacturer of towing and vehicle recovery equipment. The company manufactures the bodies of wreckers, car carriers and trailers, which are installed on truck chassis manufactured by third parties. It markets this equipment under a number of recognizable brand names, including Century, Vulcan, Chevron, Holmes, Challenger, Champion, Jige, Boniface and Eagle. Headquartered in Ooltewah, Tenn., Miller has manufacturing facilities throughout the United States, France and England. Its customer base consists of approximately 175 North American distributors, which serve all 50 states, Canada and Mexico, and 50 distributors serving other foreign markets.
          






















